Container virtualization

Install and use in the [DigitalOcean Docker tutorial](https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-and-use-docker-on-ubuntu-18-04)

**Image:** Files and config that can be instantiated.
**Container:** Instantiation of an image. Can be run/stop/start...

Basic docker:

    docker search ubuntu
    docker pull ubuntu

    # run or pull from Docker Hub and run
    docker run hello-world

Manage images

    docker images
    docker rmi [imageid]

Run and get console:

    docker run -it ubuntu

Manage containers:

    docker ps     # Show runnint containers
    docker ps -a  # Show all (stopped inc.)

    docker start [id|name]
    docker stop  [id|name]
    docker rm    [id|name]
